t.c: c Grant Elliott b Matt Henry

d.c: OUT! Boult strikes! Full and swings into Finch, he looks to flick this one but gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball balloons back to Boult who takes a simple catch. Aussie lose an early wicket and the Kiwi players are all pumped up. They have not given it up yet!

OUT! One shot too many! Banged it in short again, Warner again pulls this one but does not connect it well and the ball balloons to deep square leg where Elliott takes a good catch and Warner has to depart. Can the Kiwis script a miracle return here?

OUT! A brilliant last knock! Slower back of a length on off, Clarke looks to guide this one to third man buts gets an inside edge onto his leg stump and he has to depart. What a carrer and the entire stadium is up in an appaluase as Clarke walks on with teary eyes. Take a bow Clarke!

t.c: c Brad Haddin b James Faulkner
c Brad Haddin b James Faulkner
c Michael Clarke b Mitchell Starc
c Mitchell Starc b Mitchell Johnson

d.c: OUT! The danger man goes! Full and swinging yorker right on the money. McCullum who has smashed bowlers to all parts of the park in this World Cup is beaten for pace and the ball goes on to knock the off stump. The Aussie contingent goes up in a roar and New Zealand lose their captain for a naught.

OUT! Maxwell strikes! Short and on off stump, spins in a tad, Guptill looks to punch this one to the off side but is beaten by the spin and the ball goes on to knock the furniture. Guptill who has weathered the storm by playing out Johnson-Starc-Hazlewood goes out to the part timer Maxwell. Such a leveller this game is!

OUT! Soft dismissal! Fullish on middle, Johnson rolls his finger before delivering it. Williamson looked to flick this one but checks his shot at the last moment and the ball goes straight back to the bowler. Johnson does not miss it and New Zealand lose another wicket. The Aussies are happy and the Kiwis in some trouble here!

OUT! A brilliant catch by Haddin! Fullish and slower outside off, Taylor looks to slice this one but gets a thin outside edge to the right off the keeper. Haddin takes a superb low catch and the fielders appeal. The umpire is not convinced and refers it to the TV umpire. The replay shows it was not a bump ball and the ball just about carried to the keeper. Taylor's steady knocks comes to an end and Powerplay again sees a wicket for the fielding team.

OUT! Yorked him off! Yorker on off, Corey plays down the wrong line and the ball clips his back-pad and goes on hit the off stump. New Zealand lose two wickets in span of three balls and Aussie are back in the driver's seat.

OUT! The Kiwis are falling apart here! In the channel outside off, Ronchi looks to push at it but ends up getting a thick outside edge to it. The ball flies to first slip, Haddin looks to go for the catch but decides not to and the ball goes straight to Clarke who does not miss it. Kiwis lose Ronchi for a naught, the third of the innings and are in deep deep trouble here.

OUT! Another one back in the hut! Fullish on middle, Vettori looks to flick it to the on side, he misses and the ball goes on to clip his pad and disturb the woodwork. Vettori goes and the MCG which is looking golden today is up in a big roar.

OUT! Elliott departs! On a length on off, Elliott looks to heave it to the on side but gets a top edge that flies to the keeper. Haddin takes a simple catch and the Kiwis lose the last recognized batsman. A good innings by him though!
OUT! 4th naught of the innings! Full toss outside off, Henry punches it straight to Starc at cover-point. A bad ball but Johnson gets a wicket and New Zealand lose their ninth wicket.

OUT! Sharp from Maxwell! Boult makes room and Johnson follows him with the bouncer. He keeps it down to short mid-wicket where Maxwell is alert and has a shy at the non-striker's end. Southee fails to get back in time and the Kiwis lose their last wicket to some brilliance from Maxwell in the field. The Aussies have been brilliant in the field today. New Zealand are bowled out for 183 .
